headline: JPMorgan Acknowledges Shutting Down Trump Accounts After January 6
summary: JPMorgan Chase & Co. (NYSE: JPM) acknowledged in a court filing that it shut down bank accounts tied to President Donald Trump and several of his businesses after the Jan. 6, 2021, Capitol riot, a point now sitting at the center of Trump's $5 billion lawsuit against the lender and its chief executive.
